title: Gun safety advocates to rally at Westlake
text:
Gun safety advocates will rally in downtown Seattle Friday for stricter gun laws in Washington.
A new study shows the average gun owner now owns eight guns, double the number 20 years ago.
The rally organizer, who says she is a concerned parent, said the event is non-partisan and is neither pro-gun nor anti-gun.
The rally begins at 3 p.m. at Westlake Park and participants will march through Westlake Avenue to Lake Union Park. First Lady Trudi Inslee will attend.
State Senator David Frockt will join the rally and will speak at Lake Union Park at about 5 p.m. about the extreme risk protection bill.
For more information, see the event's Facebook page.
